  "root_text": {
    "snp4.7:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 4.7 ",
    "snp4.7:0.2": "Tissametteyyasutta ",
    "snp4.7:1.1": "“Methunamanuyuttassa, ",
    "snp4.7:1.2": "(iccāyasmā tisso metteyyo) ",
    "snp4.7:1.3": "Vighātaṁ brūhi mārisa; ",
    "snp4.7:1.4": "Sutvāna tava sāsanaṁ, ",
    "snp4.7:1.5": "Viveke sikkhissāmase”. ",
    "snp4.7:2.1": "“Methunamanuyuttassa, ",
    "snp4.7:2.2": "(metteyyāti bhagavā) ",
    "snp4.7:2.3": "Mussate vāpi sāsanaṁ; ",
    "snp4.7:2.4": "Micchā ca paṭipajjati, ",
    "snp4.7:2.5": "Etaṁ tasmiṁ anāriyaṁ. ",
    "snp4.7:3.1": "Eko pubbe caritvāna, ",
    "snp4.7:3.2": "methunaṁ yo nisevati; ",
    "snp4.7:3.3": "Yānaṁ bhantaṁva taṁ loke, ",
    "snp4.7:3.4": "hīnamāhu puthujjanaṁ. ",
    "snp4.7:4.1": "Yaso kitti ca yā pubbe, ",
    "snp4.7:4.2": "hāyate vāpi tassa sā; ",
    "snp4.7:4.3": "Etampi disvā sikkhetha, ",
    "snp4.7:4.4": "methunaṁ vippahātave. ",
    "snp4.7:5.1": "Saṅkappehi pareto so, ",
    "snp4.7:5.2": "kapaṇo viya jhāyati; ",
    "snp4.7:5.3": "Sutvā paresaṁ nigghosaṁ, ",
    "snp4.7:5.4": "maṅku hoti tathāvidho. ",
    "snp4.7:6.1": "Atha satthāni kurute, ",
    "snp4.7:6.2": "paravādehi codito; ",
    "snp4.7:6.3": "Esa khvassa mahāgedho, ",
    "snp4.7:6.4": "mosavajjaṁ pagāhati. ",
    "snp4.7:7.1": "Paṇḍitoti samaññāto, ",
    "snp4.7:7.2": "ekacariyaṁ adhiṭṭhito; ",
    "snp4.7:7.3": "Athāpi methune yutto, ",
    "snp4.7:7.4": "mandova parikissati. ",
    "snp4.7:8.1": "Etamādīnavaṁ ñatvā, ",
    "snp4.7:8.2": "Muni pubbāpare idha; ",
    "snp4.7:8.3": "Ekacariyaṁ daḷhaṁ kayirā, ",
    "snp4.7:8.4": "Na nisevetha methunaṁ. ",
    "snp4.7:9.1": "Vivekaññeva sikkhetha, ",
    "snp4.7:9.2": "etaṁ ariyānamuttamaṁ; ",
    "snp4.7:9.3": "Na tena seṭṭho maññetha, ",
    "snp4.7:9.4": "sa ve nibbānasantike. ",
    "snp4.7:10.1": "Rittassa munino carato, ",
    "snp4.7:10.2": "Kāmesu anapekkhino; ",
    "snp4.7:10.3": "Oghatiṇṇassa pihayanti, ",
    "snp4.7:10.4": "Kāmesu gadhitā pajā”ti. ",
    "snp4.7:10.5": "Tissametteyyasuttaṁ sattamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp4.7:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 4.7 ",
    "snp4.7:0.2": "With Tissametteyya ",
    "snp4.7:1.1": "“When someone indulges in sex,” ",
    "snp4.7:1.2": "said Venerable Tissametteyya, ",
    "snp4.7:1.3": "“tell us, good fellow: what trouble befalls them? ",
    "snp4.7:1.4": "After hearing your instruction, ",
    "snp4.7:1.5": "we shall train in seclusion.” ",
    "snp4.7:2.1": "“When someone indulges in sex,” ",
    "snp4.7:2.2": "replied the Buddha, ",
    "snp4.7:2.3": "“they forget their instructions ",
    "snp4.7:2.4": "and go the wrong way—",
    "snp4.7:2.5": "that is something ignoble in them. ",
    "snp4.7:3.1": "Someone who formerly lived alone ",
    "snp4.7:3.2": "and then resorts to sex ",
    "snp4.7:3.3": "is like a chariot careening off-track; ",
    "snp4.7:3.4": "in the world they call them a low, ordinary person. ",
    "snp4.7:4.1": "Their former fame and reputation ",
    "snp4.7:4.2": "also fall away. ",
    "snp4.7:4.3": "Seeing this, they’d train ",
    "snp4.7:4.4": "to give up sex. ",
    "snp4.7:5.1": "Oppressed by thoughts, ",
    "snp4.7:5.2": "they brood like a wretch. ",
    "snp4.7:5.3": "When they hear what others are saying, ",
    "snp4.7:5.4": "that sort is embarrassed. ",
    "snp4.7:6.1": "Then they lash out with verbal daggers ",
    "snp4.7:6.2": "when reproached by others. ",
    "snp4.7:6.3": "This is their great blind spot; ",
    "snp4.7:6.4": "they sink to lies. ",
    "snp4.7:7.1": "They once were considered astute, ",
    "snp4.7:7.2": "committed to the solitary life. ",
    "snp4.7:7.3": "But then they indulged in sex, ",
    "snp4.7:7.4": "dragged along by desire like a dullard. ",
    "snp4.7:8.1": "Knowing this danger ",
    "snp4.7:8.2": "in falling from a former state here, ",
    "snp4.7:8.3": "a sage would firmly resolve to wander alone, ",
    "snp4.7:8.4": "and would not resort to sex. ",
    "snp4.7:9.1": "They’d train themselves only in seclusion; ",
    "snp4.7:9.2": "this, for the noble ones, is highest. ",
    "snp4.7:9.3": "One who’d not think themselves ‘best’ due to that ",
    "snp4.7:9.4": "has truly drawn near to extinguishment. ",
    "snp4.7:10.1": "People tied to sensual pleasures envy them: ",
    "snp4.7:10.2": "the isolated, wandering sage ",
    "snp4.7:10.3": "who has crossed the flood, ",
    "snp4.7:10.4": "unconcerned for sensual pleasures.” "
  },
